    "updated_at": "2017-05-05T18:05:11Z",
    "body": "In addition to what @alexandrudima described, I found two interesting behaviors, especially the second one\r\n\r\n**Pressing any character which doesn't require composition will help with popup positioning**\r\n* Press <kbd>s</kbd>\r\n* Press <kbd>1</kbd> to accept the first suggestion\r\n* Press <kbd>1</kbd> to insert `1`\r\n* Press <kbd>s</kbd> again\r\n* Observe the suggestion list is positioned correctly, perfect.\r\n\r\nany non-compositing character helps with the positioning\r\n\r\n**if the page contains webview, then everything is good**\r\n* add both `<input>` and `<webview>` to any Electron app.\r\n* Try above all steps, everything is good."
